-- Assad Asks Russia to Broker Talks With Opposition Over Revolt, Lavrov Says
-- B y   I l y a   A r k h i p o v   a n d   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 2012-02-07T13:17:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/assad-asks-russia-to-broker-talks-with-opposition-over-revolt-lavrov-says.html
Syrian President Bashar al-Assad
asked  Russia  to broker talks with opposition groups in a bid to
end 11 months of violence in the Middle Eastern country, Russian
Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said after talks in Damascus
today, according to a pool report from Russian news service
Itar-Tass.  ``It's clear that the efforts to end the violence must be
accompanied with the initiation of a dialog among all political 
forces,'' Lavrov said. ``Today we received confirmation of the 
Syrian president's readiness to cooperate on this.''  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Arkhipov in Moscow at 
 iarkhipov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
